Who's News:
   PNC Financial Names
   James Rohr President
PNC also named Robert E. Chappell, chairman of the bank
holding company's Provident National Bank in Philadelphia, as
executive vice president of PNC. Mr. Chappell, 47, reports to
Mr. O'Brien.
   Richard L. Smoot, president of Provident National Bank,
was named chief executive of Provident. Mr. Smoot, 50, has
been acting chief executive since last summer.
   PNC also said it will start consolidating charters of
PNC's Pennsylvania banks, which the company said will improve
customer service and operating efficiency. PNC, the nation's
16th-largest bank, with $42.3 billion in assets, said it is
reviewing options for establishing a common name for the
merged banks.